⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Cameron Alexander
node AHX · AHX · ⟦Cameron Alexander:AHX:111239⟧

WHO   — Cameron Alexander — the propagandist
WHAT  — The machinery of recruitment: the adult who manufactures hatred in the vulnerable and keeps his own hands clean.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film insists the hate is taught — and Cameron is the teacher of it, the dark mirror of Sweeney.
HOW   — By spotting grief and vacancy in boys and filling it with a cause, an enemy, and a use for their anger.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I don't get my hands dirty. I find the angry boys, and I give their anger a shape. The movement runs on what I make of them.

